FEED REFERENCE LOG (for your records)
================================================================================

FEED 1 — POLYMARKET
  Auth:             None required
  Refresh:          Every 30 seconds (prices), once on load (metadata),
                    on demand (history)
  Volume filter:    $10K+ 24h
  Expected markets: 60-120 active at any time
  History:          Up to 180 days, daily close prices
  Special notes:    CORS restricted — must go through backend proxy

FEED 2 — KALSHI
  Auth:             Free API key required
  Refresh:          Every 30 seconds (prices), once on load (metadata),
                    on demand (history)
  Volume filter:    $10K+ 24h
  Expected markets: 50-90 active at any time
  Special notes:    Series structure needs flattening; show both Kalshi and
                    Polymarket separately when same event appears on both
                    (Option A); strongest platform for Cybersecurity

FEED 3 — FRED + VIX LIVE
  Auth:             Free API key required
  Refresh:          Daily at ~6pm ET (all FRED series);
                    every 5 minutes during market hours for VIX intraday
                    (9:30am-4:00pm ET, Mon-Fri via Yahoo Finance ^VIX);
                    falls back to FRED daily close outside market hours
  Key series:       VIXCLS, SP500, DGS10, FEDFUNDS, CPIAUCSL, UNRATE,
                    A191RL1Q225SBEA, RECPROUSM156N
  VIX sources:      Primary: Yahoo Finance intraday (unofficial, free, stable)
                    Fallback: FRED VIXCLS daily close (official, free)
  History:          Full historical data available going back decades
  Special notes:    VIX response includes source and market_open flag so
                    dashboard can show "Live" vs "Close" indicator

FEED 4 — GOOD JUDGMENT (GJOPEN)
  Auth:             None for Phase 1 scraping; paid contract for Phase 2
  Refresh:          Once daily
  Expected:         50-150 active questions at any time
  Special notes:    Phase 1 scraping is fragile; question matching to
                    categories requires upfront manual curation; cross-
                    reference layer needed for market vs. superforecaster
                    comparison; upgrade to GJ Pro when dashboard scales

FEED 5 — RSS NEWS
  Auth:             None required
  Sources:          13 breaking news + 4 specialist + 9 research feeds
  Refresh:          Every 5 min (breaking), 30 min (specialist),
                    daily (research)
  Special notes:    Sentiment scoring included; keyword filtering maps to
                    8 category IDs; powers Breaking News banner,
                    Intelligence Reports, and Polling & Research sections;
                    all Polling & Research sources covered via RSS except
                    RANE (requires direct data agreement)

FEED 6 — AI PLATFORMS CONSENSUS
  Auth:             Anthropic API key required at launch;
                    optional individual model keys for Phase 3 upgrades
  Refresh:          Once daily at 2:00am ET for all active markets
  Models:           Claude, DeepSeek, Gemini, GPT-4o, Grok, Mistral,
                    Perplexity (alphabetical order)
  Storage:          ai_consensus table in Supabase
  Endpoint:         GET /api/consensus/:id
  Cost estimate:    $0.50-$1.00/day at launch (Claude simulates all models)
                    $2.00-$5.00/day at Phase 3 (real APIs per model)
  Phase 1 (launch): Claude API simulates all seven model estimates
  Phase 2:          Add DeepSeek + Mistral real APIs (cheapest, easiest)
  Phase 3:          Add OpenAI (GPT-4o) + Google (Gemini) real APIs
  Phase 4:          Add Grok via xAI API when broadly available
  Special notes:    Database schema designed for drop-in model upgrades;
                    frontend checks cached result first, falls back to
                    live call if cache miss; batched in groups of 20 to
                    avoid rate limiting

FEED 7 — ENTERPRISE PULSE SURVEY
  Auth:             Anthropic API key (backend only — must be proxied)
  Refresh:          On demand (user-triggered)
  Endpoints:        POST /api/pulse/generate-single
                    POST /api/pulse/generate-custom
  Question format:  2 Likert + 2 Yes/No + 1 Open (single-topic flow);
                    mixed across 2-10 questions (custom multi-topic flow)
  Cost estimate:    ~$0.005-$0.010 per generation, negligible daily total
  Special notes:    Plain-language prompts, no jargon, no "CRO lens" or
                    "leadership vs frontline" framing; frontend allows
                    users to edit/delete/add questions after generation;
                    delivery integrations (Slack/Teams/Google Chat/Email/
                    MS Forms) are Phase 2 post-launch

FEED 8 — SIDE-PANEL SIGNAL BRIEFINGS
  Auth:             Anthropic API key (backend only — must be proxied)
  Refresh:          On demand with 6-hour cache per signal;
                    cache invalidated on >3pp probability moves
  Endpoint:         POST /api/signal-briefing
  Storage:          signal_briefings table
  Cost estimate:    $0.60-$2.00/day with caching
  Special notes:    Returns 7-point trend sparkline, 3 driver bullets,
                    one "what to watch" event pointer, and a signal color
                    hex value

FEED 9 — VIX DRIVER EXPLAINER
  Auth:             Anthropic API key (backend only — must be proxied)
  Refresh:          Every 30 min during US market hours (9:30am-4:00pm ET,
                    Mon-Fri); twice daily (9am, 5pm ET) otherwise
  Endpoint:         GET /api/vix-driver
  Storage:          vix_driver singleton cache row
  Cost estimate:    Under $0.25/day (~48 generations/day)
  Special notes:    Served to all users from cache — no per-user API
                    calls; returns event driver, 2-3 sentence detail,
                    up/down/flat direction, and approximate change


